quran[19]{c,v,t}:
  26,34,"This man,‘ he said to the nobles around him, ‘is a skilful sorcerer"
  26,35,who seeks to drive you from your land by his sorcery. What is your counsel?‘
  26,36,"They said: ‘Put them off awhile, him and his brother, and send forth criers to the cities to bring"
  26,37,every skilled enchanter to your presence.‘
  26,38,The sorcerers were gathered on an appointed day
  26,39,"and the people were asked: ‘Are you all assembled"
  26,40,We may follow the sorcerers if they win the day.‘
  26,41,"And when the sorcerers came they said to Pharaoh: ‘Shall we be rewarded if we win?‘"
  26,42,"‘Yes,‘ he answered, ‘and you shall become my favoured friends.‘"
  26,43,"Moses said to them: ‘Throw down all that you wish to throw.‘"
  26,44,"They threw down their ropes and staffs, saying: ‘By Pharaoh‘s glory, we shall surely win!‘"
  26,45,"Then Moses threw down his staff, and it swallowed up their false devices"
  26,46,The sorcerers prostrated themselves
  26,47,"saying: ‘We now believe in the Lord of the Universe"
  26,48,the Lord of Moses and Aaron.‘
  26,49,"He said: ‘Do you dare believe in him before I give you leave? He must surely be your master, who has taught you witchcraft. But you shall see. I will cut off your hands and feet on alternate sides and crucify you all.‘"
  26,50,"That cannot harm us,‘ they replied, ‘for to our Lord we shall return"
  26,51,"We hope our Lord will forgive us our sins, since we are the first who have believed.‘"
  26,52,"Then We revealed Our will to Moses, saying: ‘Set forth with My servants in the night, for you will be pursued.‘"